However, what has been newly discovered is a white paint derived from the fluorine resin of polytetrafluoroethylene (PTFE), which is used in Teflon processed frying pans.
It is a white paint that applies this Teflon effect, and it is said to be able to significantly cut heat by reflecting sunlight up to 98%.
Even in the hot summer, thanks to the white paint using Teflon, it is easy to spend time indoors without being exposed to the heat.
